cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "ShadowKV++: A Policy Controller for Waste-Aware, Admission-Controlled KV Cache Reuse in LLM Serving"
message: "If you use this repository, please cite the project."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Khemani
    given-names: Kushal
  - family-names: Leri
    given-names: Evan
  - family-names: Mittal
    given-names: Sparsh
version: 0.3.0
license: "MIT"
repository-code: "https://github.com/Kushalk0677/shadowkv"
abstract: >
  ShadowKV++ is a per-request policy controller for KV cache reuse in LLM
  serving. It scores each potential reuse event with a net-utility objective
  and admits reuse only when benefit exceeds cost plus waste, with bypass as
  a first-class action, semantic neighbourhood detection, and per-request
  telemetry for audit.
